{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's like abused women and children who feel that they deserve it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The people themselves come to think of themselves as being sub-human.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This did not happen to us, I think, largely because we were a mixed group and a group that could maintain an internal dignity because we treated each other humanely.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Occasionally, you know, there would be beatings on a completely random basis.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I told you, that was one of the advantages of not working.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By not working, we were less in daily contact with the German guards, who, again, behaved in a very capricious fashion.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of the guards, by the way, were women.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of the women-- our group had some children who survived in a mixed group.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some of the women would pick one child to whom they would bring toys, their favorite, their pet child, you know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Their maternal instinct-- instinct and their brutal instincts, they managed to keep separated, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At one point, for example, we were next to a group of Albanian Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one of my friends met a young man-- you asked if there were flirtations-- met a young man, a young, Albanian man.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They fell in love.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were separated at the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They managed to find each other after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were married, and they lived in Venezuela together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was a-- a hotel manager, and she was a-- a-- a department store manager.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I know-- [LAUGHS], you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were some.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were good friendships, deep friendships formed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, I was very friendly with two women who had-- who were extremely friendly, close to each other, because they had survived the same tragedy.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had both lost a child in the ghetto of Warsaw during the deportations.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
